{"v":1,"id":"01KXBP7ZHR0TC89MVTPM34WT7Z","ts":"2026-07-12T17:33:18.776Z","initiative":"init-statusline","session":"a0f95832-23e7-413c-83d6-7f0ab1a687a3","source":"claude-code","actor":"agent","user":"dev@jithin.io","type":"decision_logged","payload":{"because":"D4 rejected AUTO-install, not installation via init: an explicit flag is user consent, so nothing is clobbered unasked. Merge-only-when-absent + theirs-wins matches the .mcp.json/.gitattributes customized-entry precedent, and the hint fixes discoverability exactly the way the Tailwind hint does (user report Jul 12: statusline missing in other repos after init).","chose":"sofar init --statusline (informed re-test of felt-cost D4): an opt-in flag merges statusLine {type:command, command:\"sofar statusline\"} into .claude/settings.json ONLY when the key is absent — an existing statusLine, whatever its value, is the user's and wins; plain init prints a final-output opt-in hint when the project settings lack a statusLine (before the Tailwind scanner hint, which stays last), noting a project statusLine shadows a personal ~/.claude one; sofar uninit removes the entry only when it is exactly the one --statusline installs","over":"Auto-installing by default (D4's rejected clobber — a project statusLine silently shadows the user's personal statusline in every inited repo), hint-only (leaves the hand-edit friction that prompted the report), or wiring via doctor --fix (wiring belongs to init/uninit; doctor --fix is scoped to the scanner repair)"}}
